MODIFICATIONS:

1. Native builds integration
   - Modified to use native builds (https://github.com/ensody/native-builds)
     instead of prebuilt binaries
   - Updated to specify higher OpenSSL version for ML-KEM support
   - Reason: Required for ZETA SDK to support post-quantum cryptography (ML-KEM)
   - Modified files: libcurl.def
   - Modification date: January 2026
   - Modified by: EY Strategy & Transactions GmbH, licensed for gematik GmbH

2. gematik TLS compliance
   - Extended CurlClientEngineConfig to expose the following libcurl TLS options
     that were not previously available through the public API:
       · CURLOPT_SSL_CIPHER_LIST: TLS 1.2 cipher suite restriction
       · CURLOPT_TLS13_CIPHERS: TLS 1.3 cipher suite restriction
       · CURLOPT_SSL_EC_CURVES: EC curve restriction (P-256, P-384,
                                   brainpoolP256r1, brainpoolP384r1)
       · CURLOPT_SSLVERSION: minimum TLS protocol version (TLS 1.2)
       . CURLOPT_SSL_SIGNATURE_ALGORITHMS: certificate signature algorithms restriction
   - Added SslVersion enum mapping Kotlin values to libcurl CURL_SSLVERSION_*
     constants
   - Added CurlDebugCallback (top-level) via CURLOPT_DEBUGFUNCTION to log and
     validate the negotiated cipher suite, protocol version, and EC curve
     after the TLS handshake
   - Extended CurlRequestData with the new TLS fields to carry configuration
     from CurlClientEngineConfig through to CurlMultiApiHandler
   - Reason: Required to comply with gematik TLS specification.
   - Modified files: CurlClientEngineConfig.kt, CurlRequestData.kt,
     CurlMultiApiHandler.kt, CurlRaw.kt
   - New files: SslVersion.kt, tls/TlsSessionValidator.kt, tls/ValidationConfig.kt
   - Linting applied
   - Modification date: February 2026
   - Modified by: EY Strategy & Transactions GmbH, licensed for gematik GmbH


